ing: 2 (15 ounce) cans sliced peaches, peaches cut into thirds
des: "This is a go-to recipe for me, and it's great for summer cookouts served with ice cream. Very quick and easy to make and most people have the ingredients in their pantries already. The more brown sugar you use on top, the more 'crumble' you will have."
ins:
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
Pour peaches into a 9x13-inch baking dish. Spread cake mix in an even layer over peaches. Cover cake mix with butter slices and spread brown sugar over the top.
Bake in the preheated oven until golden and bubbling, about 30 minutes.
